late the investment by using the following components:\n\n1. **Technology and Infrastructure Costs (Operating Expense):** This is the primary line item capturing the R&D payroll and infrastructure costs (servers, networking, data center depreciation) explicitly tied to the satellite network development.\n2. **Purchases of Property and Equipment (Investing Cash Flow):** This captures the capital expenditures (CapEx) associated with building the satellite network. An analyst would look at the total CapEx and attempt to isolate the portion attributable to Kuiper.\n3. **Property and Equipment Sub-Categories (Balance Sheet):** Using the XBRL tags provided (`amzn:ServersAndNetworkingEquipmentMember`, `us-gaap:ConstructionInProgressMember`, `us-gaap:OtherCapitalizedPropertyPlantAndEquipmentMember`), an analyst can track specific asset classes where Kuiper-related capital is likely being capitalized.\n4. **Segment Information (Note 10):** An analyst would examine the segment breakdown (North America, International, AWS) to see if Kuiper costs are being allocated to a specific segment (e.g., AWS for cloud/network services or International for global broadband) or if they are buried in corporate/unallocated expenses.',
