k Subscribers across 164 countries, territories, and other markets. This is up approximately 105% from 5.0 million subscribers a year prior. \n*   **Mobile Users:** The segment also serves approximately 7.4 million monthly unique devices with satellite-to-mobile texting and voice services.\n*   **Revenue:** For the three months ended March 31, 2026, the Connectivity segment generated revenue of $3,257 million. For the full year 2025, it generated $11,387 million, representing a 49.8% year-over-year growth.\n\n**Connectivity Segment Capex vs. Historical Periods**\nThe company is in a heavy infrastructure investment stage for the Connectivity segment, with capital expenditures increasing year-over-year to fund satellite and ground equipment expansion:\n*   **Q1 2026 vs. Q1 2025:** Capex increased by $518 million, rising to $1,332 million for the three months ended March 31, 2026, up from $814 million in the prior-year quarter.\n*   **Full Year 2025 vs. 2024:** Capex increased by $680 million to $4,178 million in 2025, up from $3,498 million in 2024.\n*   **Full Year 2024 vs. 2023:** Capex increased by $1,043 million to $3,498 million in 2024, up from $2,455 million in 2023.\n*   **Drivers of Capex:** The filing notes that the increases in each year-over-year period were "primarily driven by higher satellite and ground equipment costs as we continue to increase our number of satellites and grow our satellite network."',
